\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 650, \"output\": 1303, \"cacheRead\": 43008, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 44961, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"stop\", \"timestamp\": 1778169483352, \"responseId\": \"resp_05f971a8609c024f0169fcb68cd7ec819ca52508f914c3e55d\"}}\n[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Evaluating error handling**\\n\\nI’m looking to use a positive approach, but I need to consider what happens if the handler gets a UOE and the ProcessHandle reflection fails. If the MXBean name isn’t in the expected format, then the helper rethrows UOE, which would cause the test to fail. But maybe it's still worth keeping the ProcessHandle since it probably remains available. I see how this could get complicated—let’s keep it simple!\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_05f971a8609c024f0169fcb68daa18819c86abf2965ae6512f\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp_LaaNk0i0cDRgQnQTycapls1tOiRwRgf92zq0GegV0jDY2SkZgYblRnnv-03PfJhBBfNLyDsXMVWoqC14uCQ1FK4TNhTJ1X-MIy5mMQ0ucjgWjzdT_OwEv0Gu5CjNj6JhgNqMKuGx_AYAnJLXa5IKA_9fX6nf2b-bzYaOB1AOFAkWX5dW8tSSAvLWEcD2oOWlq2pltCbW2BGhravKCsskJDTSSzSogY47Q-jANa0M7aE0_xBReKxY25cr9OcQH5l_ypxQUmx3weCjcPuO7kjYUnDk1Z9_J_bLhfi3SnnrXCoJ6C0qh_GDf08nnV_ZjhpEUszsdUFjPKIsq2ojzzgoNLR6m8NBR-PAy0WBw_TrO6yhp0KvNuNEOn44LrWp7uPvqcqWRocZ3NDNUcLGaRdSSCpyZhsWDq6lIgWJSY9f6IdO_5aCqiq7NQybL6Ctzd_HJi_aT9Iwji2ka636AHtJ7D_KlV9qgU6AwFxVcOjZYal8JkP8gnSkWTCmRWlnkPAdF-kBdx98Jdha8AiXAmM12WKVwgrvVcC6Ix-ruPqhWKNia_l3tp2EAjZBzdXdSrWSljZ1OccQNgz-jOFNHFGqGHIYPIDMoTXLc1DJFJ0soU6paW8FDnUGqxLzxDOFI7Kr7NGEgNJUkY4Adfa9NBpOwVKGCC7-XVLby3PDjVg5sMMfI2_VzpnKCbByIsE3fzTIjhWhZVM3oz9le4oDXO0LAaGnA6qwYUtvlL_swh9ouKTbsCfLispydGXpYvyqG1yxijG9fqRMAv42OB81lL-W5S55AR3NlxM00TYyOUtqH89H221EKKfiVICge2gPgqBhfaLSEr5b3gIvSbSOLHODQYpZdRc4U98GkyyuoHdDo1_CPZJhbpcVbgyT1YzCGO2G6gIx9n1wrv9o5zc9skbixf